snippet.textDisplay: So that sir bag you mentioned wrong color. Correct do not try to paint it. But here is a suggestion you might try and if done properly you will never tell it was ran brown and not the black you made it. I used to work in my uncle's upholstery shop and we did recoloring and touchups on faded or discolored Vinyl and naughahyde tops on cars and dashes and even the seat coverings and mid consoles. You need to go buy a specialty chem and color kit for plastics and vinyls. under $75 and is amazing. My niece spilled nail polish recently on my mom's brand new couch it's dark brown and the nail polish removed the color and big white spot on one the cushions . I had this kit now since 1997 to color a vinyl top on a New Yorker. You can't even tell it was recolored. The couch that is. I had my niece in tears when I first saw what happened . I said to her you know how many Naughas they had to kill to make that couch and there extinct now and I can't get the naughydes to fix it...............I'm a ass LOL.
